quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  3,16,"Who say, \"O our Lord! we have indeed believed; pardon us our sins, and keep us from the torment of the fire"
  3,17,"The patient, and the truthful, the lowly, and the charitable, and they who seek pardon at each daybreak"
  3,18,"God witnesseth that there is no god but He: and the angels, and men endued with knowledge, stablished in righteousness, proclaim \"There is no god but He, the Mighty, the Wise"
  3,19,"The true religion with God is Islam: and they to whom the Scriptures had been given, differed not till after \"the knowledge\" had come to them, and through mutual jealousy. But as for him who shall not believe in the signs of God - God will be prompt to reckon with him"
  3,20,"If they shall dispute with thee, then SAY: I have surrendered myself to God, as have they who follow me. SAY to those who have received the Book, and to the common folk, Do ye surrender yourselves unto God? If they become Muslims, then are they guided aright: but if they turn away - thy duty is only preaching; and God's eye is on His servants"
  3,21,"But to those who believe not in the signs of God, and unjustly slay the prophets, and slay those men who enjoin uprightness, - announce an afflictive chastisement"
  3,22,"These are they whose works come to nought in this world, and in the next; and none shall they have to help them"